# section_guidance.txt — Section Guidance File Template
# Target size: 150–300 chars (truncated to 500 chars at load time)
# Purpose: Per-section LLM writing guidance — structure, tone, prohibited inventions
# File name: {section_key}.txt  (e.g., executive_summary.txt, features.txt)
#
# AUTHORING GUIDE — Four elements (all optional but recommended):
#   Structure: What format/outline to use (bullets, table, paragraphs, subsections)
#   Required:  Inputs from project metadata or context (use [PLACEHOLDER] notation)
#   Infer:     What the AI can safely assume from standard patterns
#   Avoid:     What the AI must NOT invent or overcommit to
#   Tone:      Audience-appropriate register (management / contractual / technical)
#
# BEST PRACTICES:
#   - Keep to 150–300 chars for the live file (be dense, no redundancy)
#   - Use [PLACEHOLDER] for project-specific values that vary per project
#   - Reference template section headings where helpful ("Template: FAT Condition")
#   - One line per guidance element is sufficient; semicolons for compound items
#   - Do NOT duplicate guidance already present in shared context files
#
# DELETE this header block and replace below with actual section guidance
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Structure: [FORMAT — e.g., 2-3 paragraphs / bullet list / table with sr_no+column+column]
Required: [METADATA_FIELD_1], [METADATA_FIELD_2]; use [PLACEHOLDER] if absent.
Infer: [STANDARD_PATTERN_1]; [STANDARD_PATTERN_2].
Avoid: [PROHIBITED_INVENTION_1]; [PROHIBITED_INVENTION_2].
Tone: [REGISTER — e.g., management-level / contractual / technical-factual].
[PRODUCT_TYPE]-specific: [ANY_PRODUCT_SPECIFIC_GUIDANCE].
